  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Evaluation metricWe use the standard multi-class classification metrics, such as Matthews Correlation Coefficient (MCC), micro and macro averages of recall/sensitivity, precision, and F1score, to validate the performance of GPT-4V on this dataset.",
    "Radiology DatasetWe use the CheXpert [13] dataset for evaluating GPT-4V's capabilities on radiology diagnosis.",
    "This is a publicly available dataset that contains 224,316 chest radiographs of 65,240 patients, labeled for the presence of 14 common chest radiographic observations.",
    "We follow the setting from CheXpert competition, which limited classification to five diseases based on clinical relevance: (a) Atelectasis, (b) Cardiomegaly, (c) Consolidation, (d) Edema, and (e) Pleural Effusion.",
    "The test split of the CheXpert dataset is used, and it contains 668 images from 500 patients."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Radiology DatasetWe use the CheXpert [13] dataset for evaluating GPT-4V's capabilities on radiology diagnosis."
  ]
